---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — David Henzel"
  description="David Henzel is a serial entrepreneur with 20+ years of experience building companies across SaaS, B2B services, AI consulting, and community."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-16">
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-12">

      <!-- Speaking/stage photo placeholder -->
      <div class="shrink-0">
        <div
          class="w-full md:w-72 h-80 bg-neutral-100 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center"
          aria-label="David Henzel speaking photo placeholder"
        >
          <div class="text-center">
            <svg class="w-14 h-14 text-neutral-300 mx-auto mb-3" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6.827 6.175A2.31 2.31 0 015.186 7.23c-.38.054-.757.112-1.134.175C2.999 7.58 2.25 8.507 2.25 9.574V18a2.25 2.25 0 002.25 2.25h15A2.25 2.25 0 0021.75 18V9.574c0-1.067-.75-1.994-1.802-2.169a47.865 47.865 0 00-1.134-.175 2.31 2.31 0 01-1.64-1.055l-.822-1.316a2.192 2.192 0 00-1.736-1.039 48.774 48.774 0 00-5.232 0 2.192 2.192 0 00-1.736 1.039l-.821 1.316z" />
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M16.5 12.75a4.5 4.5 0 11-9 0 4.5 4.5 0 019 0zM18.75 10.5h.008v.008h-.008V10.5z" />
            </svg>
            <p class="text-xs text-neutral-400">Stage photo coming soon</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Name + tagline -->
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 mb-4 leading-tight">
          David Henzel
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
          Entrepreneur. Founder. Coach.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bio -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-neutral-400 mb-8">About</p>
      <div class="space-y-5 text-base text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          David Henzel is a serial entrepreneur with over 20 years of experience building companies. Born and raised in Germany, he started his first company as a teenager — a spark that set the direction for everything that followed. He's been based in the US for many years, building ventures at the intersection of technology, people, and purpose.
        </p>
        <p>
          His first major company was Octeth, an email infrastructure platform. From there, he built a portfolio of businesses that compound on one another — each one solving a real problem, each one informed by what came before. He founded <a href="https://ltvplus.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-neutral-900 underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-60 transition-opacity">LTVplus</a>, an outsourced customer experience firm that grew to over 200 team members, serving companies that needed world-class support without building it entirely in-house.
        </p>
        <p>
          When David began coaching other founders, he couldn't find a platform built for how serious coaches actually work — so he built one. <a href="https://upcoach.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-neutral-900 underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-60 transition-opacity">upcoach</a> is the result: a coaching platform now used by thousands of coaches and clients worldwide.
        </p>
        <p>
          Today he runs 10 companies across SaaS, B2B services, AI consulting, and community — and is actively involved in building each one. He's not a passive investor; he's a hands-on founder who believes the best companies come from leaders who are doing their own inner work.
        </p>
        <p>
          Outside of building companies, David is deeply committed to meditation, inner work, and what he calls conscious leadership — the idea that how you lead internally shapes everything you create externally. That commitment gave rise to the <a href="/love-not-fear" class="text-neutral-900 underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-60 transition-opacity">Love Not Fear framework</a>, which now underpins how he builds, leads, and helps other founders grow.
        </p>
        <div class="pt-2">
          <a
            href="/companies"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-neutral-900 hover:opacity-60 transition-opacity"
          >
            View all 10 companies
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5L21 12m0 0l-7.5 7.5M21 12H3" />
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Philosophy -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-neutral-400 mb-6">Philosophy</p>
      <blockquote class="text-3xl font-medium text-neutral-900 tracking-tight leading-snug mb-6">
        "Lead with love, not fear."
      </blockquote>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-base text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        <p>
          The Love Not Fear framework is David's guiding principle — in business, in leadership, and in life. It starts from a simple observation: most of the bad decisions founders make come from fear. Fear of failure, fear of judgment, fear of losing control. And most of the best ones come from a deeper place — care, courage, and genuine purpose.
        </p>
        <p>
          Love Not Fear isn't soft. It's a practical framework for how to hire, how to lead teams, how to make hard calls, and how to build something that lasts. It draws on David's own journey through meditation and inner work, and on the patterns he's seen across hundreds of conversations with founders.
        </p>
      </div>
      <a
        href="/love-not-fear"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-900 text-white text-sm font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-700 transition-colors"
      >
        Explore the framework
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5L21 12m0 0l-7.5 7.5M21 12H3" />
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Media mentions -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 border-t border-neutral-100">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-neutral-400 mb-8">Featured in</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      {[
        { name: 'Forbes', url: 'https://forbes.com' },
        { name: 'Inc.', url: 'https://inc.com' },
        { name: 'Fast Company', url: 'https://fastcompany.com' },
        { name: 'HuffPost', url: 'https://huffpost.com' },
        { name: 'YEC', url: 'https://yec.co' },
        { name: 'The Next Web', url: 'https://thenextweb.com' },
        { name: 'VentureBeat', url: 'https://venturebeat.com' },
      ].map((outlet) => (
        <a
          href={outlet.url}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-block px-4 py-2 border border-neutral-200 rounded-md text-sm font-medium text-neutral-500 hover:border-neutral-400 hover:text-neutral-800 transition-all duration-150"
        >
          {outlet.name}
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
